		"description": "<p>Also at 3rd level, when you have disadvantage on ability checks or saving throws, you gain an expertise die. When you have disadvantage on an attack roll, you add your proficiency bonus to damage. Whenever you have disadvantage on any die roll, you can spend 2 exertion to roll normally instead. Starting at 11th level you can instead spend 4 exertion to turn the disadvantage into advantage.</p><p>Additionally, whenever you roll with advantage or disadvantage and roll the same result on both die, you become emboldened. Until the end of your next turn, your next weapon attack deals an additional damage die.</p>",
